<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                        <head>51. Telegram 428 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d51fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/8–955.
                                Confidential; Priority. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>; substance approved by <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1">Dulles</persName> and Morton (H). The time of
                                transmission is illegible.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-09">August 9,
                                1955</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d51-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d51-1"/>
                        <p>428. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Your 369. You are authorized in your discretion to brief members
                            congressional Atomic Energy Group on discussions to date regarding
                            civilians. You may also give them general idea of what is involved in
                            representation issue but you should avoid mention name of any third
                            country in this connection.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1"><hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>